Please translate each line literally into English.
7 E io più lieve che per l’altre foci 8 m’andava, sì che sanz’ alcun labore 9 seguiva in sù li spiriti veloci;
10 quando Virgilio incominciò: «Amore, 11 acceso di virtù, sempre altro accese, 12 pur che la fiamma sua paresse fore;
13 onde da l’ora che tra noi discese 14 nel limbo de lo ’nferno Giovenale, 15 che la tua affezion mi fé palese,
16 mia benvoglienza inverso te fu quale 17 più strinse mai di non vista persona, 18 sì ch’or mi parran corte queste scale.

query.result:
7 And I, lighter than through the other narrows, 8 went on, so that without any fatigue 9 I followed the swift spirits upward;
10 when Virgil began: “Love, 11 kindled by virtue, always kindles another, 12 provided that its flame appears outwardly;
13 whence from the hour that Juvenal descended among us 14 into the limbo of Hell, 15 which made your affection for me manifest,
16 my goodwill toward you was such 17 as never bound closer two people who had never met, 18 so that now these stairs seem short to me.

46 How many will rise up with shorn hair 47 through ignorance, which takes away 48 the repentance for this sin in life and at the end!
49 And know that the fault which directly opposes 50 a certain sin, dries up its greenness here along with it;
51 therefore, if I have been among those people 52 who weep for avarice, in order to purge myself, 53 I have encountered its opposite».

