query.result:
88 And before I led the Greeks to the rivers
89 of Thebes in my poetry, I received baptism;
90 but through fear I remained a secret Christian,

91 outwardly showing paganism for a long time;
92 and this lukewarmness made me circle the fourth circle
93 more than the fourth hundredth.

112 One sees her who showed Langia;
113 there is the daughter of Tiresias, and Thetis,
114 and Deidamia with her sisters».

115 Both poets were now silent, 116 newly attentive to looking around, 117 free from climbing and from walls;
118 and already four of the handmaids of the day 119 were left behind, and the fifth was at the chariot pole, 120 still raising its burning horn upward,
121 when my leader said: “I believe that at the end 122 we must turn our right shoulders, 123 going around the mountain as we are accustomed to do”.

